"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-17-Paris-2024-A-game-changer-for-gender-equality-in-sports--1vj11RbJ42c-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  The Paris 2024 Olympic Games are said to be the first Games to achieve full gender parity. There are equal numbers of female and male athletes participating in the Games for the first time ever \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 that's 5,250 each. It took 128 years for the Olympics to achieve this goal. Is this a turning point for gender equality in sports? Click the video to find out!  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"